data.title: Monthly Market Update | October 2021
data.description:
Overview

1. The Federal Reserve (the “Fed”) signals gradual tapering by year-end
 
2. Central banks keep rates low despite inflationary signs
 
3. Growth slowed by Delta variant and supply chain bottlenecks
 
4. Eurozone economy surpasses the US and China in Q3
 
5. Oil rallies amid tight supply and surging demand worldwide
 
6. Equities rise despite mixed earnings

7. Apple and Amazon miss earnings amid supply-chain constraints

8. Sentiment declines amid inflation and supply chain concerns
